title: school football | Top performers
text:
Rushing • Jordan Leasure, Amanda-Clearcreek
Rushed for 263 yards and two touchdowns on 29 carries and added a receiving score, two-point conversion, interception, fumble recovery and blocked a field-goal attempt in a 29-28 win over Logan Elm.
>> Videos | Football highlights from around central Ohio
>> High-school football results, box scores from Week 8
• Daniel Bangura, Harvest Prep
Rushed for 255 yards and three touchdowns on eight carries in a 54-12 win over Grove City Christian.
• Benny Snell, Westerville Central
Rushed for 210 yards and two touchdowns on 19 carries in a 42-7 win over Westerville South.
Passing • Patrick Robinson, Hamilton Township
Passed for 398 yards and four touchdowns in a 34-0 win over Bloom-Carroll.
• Gabe Caldwell, Licking Heights
Passed for 388 yards and six touchdowns in a 58-13 win over Lakewood.
• Gunnar Hoak, Dublin Coffman
Passed for 360 yards and a touchdown in a 38-13 win over Westland.
• Ridge Durbin, Danville
Passed for 248 yards and two touchdowns and ran for three scores in a 49-6 win over Loudonville.
Receiving • Eric Bradford, Dublin Coffman
Had nine receptions for 183 yards in the Westland victory.
• Derek Dunnagan, Hilliard Bradley
Had 10 receptions for 176 yards and a touchdown in a 35-0 win over Westerville North.
